Welcome to \033[33m\033[1mCalculatore\033[0m, a simple command-line calculator with a unique feature: it understands words as operators. This is my first program and started as a fun experiment to see if I could build a calculator.
.BR
### \033[1mHow It Works\033[0m
.BR
Calculatore performs arithmetic operations using either symbols or words. After each calculation, the result will be used as the starting point for the next calculation unless you type \033[33m\033[1m"reset"\033[0m.
.BR
### \033[1mExamples\033[0m
.BR
- \033[33m1 plus 3.5\033[0m
  Adds 3.5 to 1, resulting in 4.5.
.BR
- \033[33mdivided by 6\033[0m
  Divides the previous result (4.5) by 6, resulting in 0.75.
.BR
### \033[1mSupported Operators\033[0m
.BR
You can use the following operators:
.BR
- \033[33m\033[1mAddition\033[0m: \033[33mplus\033[0m or \033[33m+\033[0m
.BR
- \033[33m\033[1mSubtraction\033[0m: \033[33mminus\033[0m or \033[33m-\033[0m
.BR
- \033[33m\033[1mDivision\033[0m: \033[33mdivided by\033[0m or \033[33m/\033[0m
.BR
- \033[33m\033[1mMultiplication\033[0m: \033[33mtimes\033[0m or \033[33m*\033[0m
.BR
### \033[1mAdditional Commands\033[0m
.BR
- \033[33m"reset"\033[0m: Resets the calculator to start fresh.
.BR
- \033[33mCTRL + C\033[0m: Exits the program.
.BR
### \033[1mUsage\033[0m
.BR
To run the calculator, simply type \033[33mcalculatore\033[0m in the terminal.
.BR
Just enter your calculations directly into the terminal!
.BR
For example:
.BR
- \033[33m1 plus 3.5\033[0m
.BR
- \033[33mdivided by 6\033[0m
.BR
- \033[33mreset\033[0m
